  "texts": [
    "And we still haven't explained how subject, predicate, predication, and truth-values emerge out of mere miming and mirroring.",
    "But arbitrary symbols and the \"propositional attitude\" clearly emerged triumphant eventually, in the evolution of human language, and then it all migrated to the auditory/oral modality where the scope for referent iconicity was even narrower (and eventually also to the written, printed and online modality).",
    "So, is all trace and scope for iconicity (other than in onomatopoeia and the sign language of the deaf) gone?",
    "and has all scope for iconicity vanished?",
    "At the word/referent level, probably."
